The paper discusses case studies in software engineering, which is the primary focus of the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper also discusses practical challenges in conducting case studies, which could fall under the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category. Additionally, the paper mentions the socio-economic environments in which case studies are conducted, which could be relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the difficulty of running large, controlled experiments, which could be relevant to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) category.
